  "prompt": "All things considered, did Bill Clinton do well as a president?",
  "response": "Bill Clinton's presidency, from 1993 to 2001, is generally viewed as a period of economic prosperity and relative peace. Here's a look at some key aspects:\n\n*   **Economy:** Clinton presided over a period of significant economic growth. The budget was balanced, and the national debt saw a surplus. Unemployment rates also declined.\n*   **Domestic Policy:** Key initiatives included the Violent Crime Control and Law Enforcement Act, the Don't Ask, Don't Tell policy regarding gays in the military, and welfare reform.\n*   **Foreign Policy:** Clinton engaged in peacekeeping efforts in the Balkans and intervened in the Bosnian War. He also played a role in the Israeli-Palestinian peace process.\n\nHowever, his presidency was also marked by controversies, including the Whitewater scandal and his impeachment proceedings related to his affair with Monica Lewinsky. These events led to significant political division.\n\nHistorians and political scientists have different perspectives on Clinton's legacy. Some emphasize his economic achievements and centrist policies, while others focus on the ethical questions raised by the scandals. Public opinion polls during and after his presidency reflected this divide, with some polls showing high approval ratings and others revealing deep disapproval.",
